   @{"   Foreword  " LINK "ForewordL"} there was long ago an idea...
   @{" Installation" LINK "InstallationL"} Components to make the Softwaresystem start
   @{"Configuration" LINK "ConfigurationL"} Start before runing the mainprog.
   @{" The program " LINK "The programL"} Moduls that make effects ;-)
   @{"   History   " LINK "HistoryL"} Is structured to...
   @{"  Register   " LINK "RegisterL"} This program is Shareware
   @{"   General   " LINK "GeneralL"} non-warranty,conditions,future

This is the first english and german version. The hole guide was concepted, 
written and generated by SKM.

There exists one problem by using SKM with the feature @{"Read Drives or Dirs" LINK "ReadoutDrivesL"}
You have to install the AmigaOS "list" command (Amigaos 3.5) version: 43.2 or higher.
The list command version 37.5 (AmigaOS 3.1) isn't work absolutly perfect. It's not a
problem of SKM, but of the very old list-command from 1991!

@ENDNODE


@NODE "ForewordL" "Foreword"
@TOC "MAIN"
I'm Amiga-User since 1994 and this project I started 1997. Not all time through,
but here and there, I have the time.

My first language I learned was CanDo. The enlargement of it is AV1-language.
With this I could do most of it, I thought SKM should have on board.

Earlier it was for me unpossible to think that programing could be one of
my favourite things. But it was with CanDo easy to generate in few hours
helpful, individual applications and so this eagerness hold on over years.

The Amiga, the creativ people and nevertheless the OS ... is always a pleasure.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "InstallationL" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"
The dir with SkM and the components, copy to a drive or disc.
After copied, please install the system-components by using the
install-script in the dir of SkM.

At least execute the configurationprogram named "editprefs".
It's important to run the configurationprog. on account of starting 
SkM... it dosen't work if not ;-)

content:
Skriptmanager/Editor
Skriptmanager/EditPrefs 
Skriptmanager/Libs/Cando.library  
Skriptmanager/Libs/Powerpacker00.library
Skriptmanager/Libs/Powerpacker20.library
Skriptmanager/Rexx/GetWord.rexx
Skriptmanager/Rexx/LoadScript.rexx
Skriptmanager/install-libs68000
Skriptmanager/install-libs68020
Skriptmanager/Skriptmanager.guide
Skriptmanager/SkriptmanagerE.guide
Skriptmanager/Cookie.txt   
Skriptmanager/Spell.DAT
Skriptmanager/SpellE.DAT
Skriptmanager/Skmtask

Will run on:
680x Amiga with 1MB FastRam and AmigaOS 2.0.

If drives will be captured: there have to be 4MB Ram onboard. 
Moreover you need drivespace; such much space ever large the medium
is to have all data grabed. Normaly about 1-6MB.
  

Testes with:
1. Amiga1200/ Blizzard1260 / 32MBFastram / AGA / OS 3.5
2. P 3 500MHz Win98SE and WinUAE

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ConfigurationL" "Configuration"
@TOC "MAIN"
Before starting the mainprog please run EditPref placed in the main
directory with SKM.

Editprefs setup the SKM, provide it with information about:

@{APEN 3}font: @{APEN 1}
the font SKM should work with (use no Proportional-Font like times. Use FixedWidth
fonts like courier or helvetica)

@{APEN 3}height:@{APEN 1}
height of font

@{APEN 3}Multiview:@{APEN 1}
the program that should show the Amiga-Guide 

@{APEN 3}RexxMast:@{APEN 1}
the path & filename of RexxMast

@{APEN 3}Rexx Com.:@{APEN 1}
Enter only the path of the tool-programs of Arexx. Usually stored in SYS:Rexxc

@{APEN 3}RexxSkripte:@{APEN 1}
if you choose to establish a project-directory for arexx-scripts
then report here where to find. It's for starting and finding a script quicker.
Enter only the path.

@{APEN 3}Skmtask:@{APEN 1}
This field is very important. Here you have to put in the entry (Program),
that starts the Binary, Pics, Programs, Music paste in a Amiga-Guide.
(Either you can try PowerGuide from AminetCD) 
It's very important to look over @{"SKMTASK" LINK "SKMTASKL"} if you think to
catalog drives or dirs.

@{APEN 3}Projekt:@{APEN 1}
Enter here the projectfile you work with every day. The ending of the file have
to be ".guide". After the AmigaGuide-File can called by the Menu: 
"User /  Project---.guide " 

@{APEN 3}Skripte:@{APEN 1}
Enter here the 5 scriptfiles you think to work often with. You can start this
scripts by the Menu: "Scripts /  Scripts " 


@ENDNODE

@NODE "The programL" "The program"
@TOC "MAIN"
All Guidebuilding-Components: @{"Guidebuilding" LINK "GuidebL"}
The Guidebuilder: @{"Guidebuilder" LINK "GuidebuilderL"}
The Linkmanager:  @{" Linkmanager" LINK "LinkmanagerL"}
